RAF planes (and nearly all WWII airplanes in general) did not have ejector seats and thus pilots could not  from their planes. Pilots at the time had to climb out or flip the plane upside down and drop themselves out to escape, if they weren't incapacitated or the plane wasn't spiraling. Ejector seats weren't widely used until after the war, when jets took over the skies.





